A default earns a node when writing it down changes the code, and stays silent
when it only names what would have been written anyway.

Sorts ascend unless the text says otherwise.
Functions return a new value rather than mutating their argument, unless the text
says otherwise.
Comparisons use the natural ordering of the elements.
Empty input is valid input and yields the empty result.

These are already assumed, so restating one as a node buys nothing. Write down the
assumption that overrides them, because that one bends the code and the reader must
be able to see it and delete it.
